Wealth Management
What we offer
Investing your wealth
Investment products
Traditional funds




Traditional funds

A simple, flexible way to diversify.








Traditional funds are mutual funds that pool your money with other investors’ money. There are funds that invest in all kinds of assets – from stocks and shares to bank deposits. They cover major markets around the world. As with all investment, traditional funds can fall in value as well as rise. You may get back less than you invested.
No need to manage your own investments
Traditional funds are ideal if you don't want to manage your own investments directly. Experienced, seasoned investment professionals manage the funds and make decisions on your behalf.
Leading fund managers 
The global presence of Barclays gives you access to some of the best managers and funds around the world.
Performance monitoring
We monitor all of our traditional funds to ensure they meet strict performance criteria. This means meeting with and assessing the portfolio managers and all key personnel involved in running the funds










Equity funds     

Investing in major stock markets
These funds invest in the major stock markets, including London, New York, Hong Kong, China and South East Asia.

Investments in global stock markets
No need to manage your portfolio
Funds suited to your strategy
Only take risks you’re comfortable with
Diversify your portfolio
For medium to long-term investing
Risk of loss of capital







Fixed income funds     

Regular income and access to the bond market
Also known as bond funds, these investments offer you a regular income and a chance to diversify your portfolio.

Designed for a consistent, regular income
For retirement planning
Excellent diversification for your portfolio
Strategies to suit your goals
For medium to long-term investing
Risk of loss of capital







Sector funds     

Focusing on particular industries
Sector funds invest in companies that operate in a particular industry or sector. Our sector funds also include commodity funds.

Invest in a single sector
A range of carefully selected funds
Follow your individual strategy
Be aware of the risk of loss. Single sector investment is subject to higher risk unless you diversify your portfolio
For medium to long-term investing
Risk of loss of capital







Money Market Funds     

A shorter-term lower-risk solution
For shorter-term investment, these lower-risk funds can offer you higher interest rates than savings accounts, although with a risk to your capital.

Lower-risk, short-term investments
Diverse portfolios to suit you
Highly experienced fund managers
Save by pooling your resources
Risk of loss of capital







Exchange Traded Funds     

Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs) for flexibility
Our exchange traded funds (ETFs) offer the portfolio diversification of a fund, but can be traded like shares.

Diversification for your portfolio
Easy, flexible trading
Ideal for diverse small investments
For medium to long-term investing
Risk of loss of capital












